en_1731073_0	The “Presidential Commission of Inquiry to Investigate and Inquire into the Issuance of Treasury Bonds” visited the Central Bank of Sri Lanka on the morning of March 01.
en_1731073_1	The Commission made a site visit to the Central Bank of Sri Lanka to observe an auction.
en_1731073_2	Meanwhile, a Treasury Bill auction worth Rs.
en_1731073_3	24 billion took place at the Central Bank today, March 01.
en_1731073_4	The Central Bank said, Treasury Bills which were auctioned are to mature in periods of three months, six months and a year.
